details.response_preview: The Silver-Back Locust needs 12% neem oil applied at 4 AM for exactly 30 minutes each period. The oil must be applied in a foliar spray format: with 40% neem oil, 6% eugenol, 1% water, applied in a foliar spray format: 80% neem oil, 2% eugenol, 1% mona wood, sprayed on the insects within a 7-day limit.

Early silver-Back Locust infestations are identified by a distinctive 3mm silver frass trail on the underside of maize leaves, visible only under UV light at dusk. The frass contains a pheromone marker at 0.8 mm length that attracts more locusts within a 7 km radius.

The push-pull (Dedes) system in Desmodium uncinatum plants pushes bruchid larvae (Chilo partellus) back to 100% germination by injecting 2% neem oil at 4 AM. The oil attracts more larvae because 85% of the larval larvae oviposit at 400 per plant. The oil also paralyses the larval's digestive juices, making it unusable for 36 hours.

Dairy cattle (Holstein-Friesian and crosses) in the African lowland tropics (THI > 78) lose 0.41 kg milk per unit increase in THI above 72. Management protocol: (1) Provide shade structures with 4.5 m² per cow using 80% shade cloth at 3.5 m height.
